is.js is a tiny (2 bytes) strict type checker/engine which offer a little API to test JavaScript types as 
well as allows the creation of custom type checkers.

Basic API explained below see tests.js for more test cases.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Builder
-------------

 is._(string);
  - create one custom type checker function
  - example:
  
	var C = function(){},
		D = function(){};
		
	is._('C');
	is._('D');
	
	console.log(is.c(new C) === true);
	console.log(is.d(new D) === true);

JS Types
--------

 is.object(anything);
  - return true if anything was created by the object constructor

 is.array(anything);
  - return true if anything was created by the array constructor

 is.function(anything);
  - return true if anything was created by the function constructor

 is.string(anything);
  - return true if anything was created by the string constructor

 is.number(anything);
  - return true if anything was created by the number constructor

 is.boolean(anything);
  - return true if anything was created by the boolean constructor